Text: What is this statue...?
Looks like this is the end of the road.
All this way...just for an altar and a statue...

...But the substance from the facility...is mixed in
here and there... How interesting...
Don't touch anything.
Aww...
No "aww"s.
Hey, doesn't this statue look a bit like Lady Alpha?

It does! It looks like her! But the statue lady looks
a little older!
Just what is this statue...
Lady Alpha! You shouldn't touch it unprotected—
Huh... Ah?!
I-I'm sorry. I shouldn't touch it!

But if you touch it...then it's okay for me to
touch it too...
Eta, can you have a look at this glowing panel?
Hmm...let me see...
Oh... These are more of Sergey's records...

I'm...surprised someone who looked as he did left
this many records to be found. I'm not sure whether
to call him careless or diligent.

What if that's just how he was raised? Seems like
you couldn't run a vineyard if you weren't detail-
oriented.

No matter what I try, I can't proceed beyond this
point. It appears I need something from a direct
descendant called "genetic data."

It would be ridiculous to suggest that I locate a
descendant of the elf from this statue among
all the elves living in the world.

"Genetic data" seems to be a standardized key used
here in this place called the "Sanctuary," but since
it seems to have no bearing on my research of Malak
at present, I'm ignoring it.

Though the Cult of Diablos utilizes the technology of
the Sanctuary, I surmise that they don't understand
this place in its entirety.

In fact, not one of the Rounds is aware of the
location of this Sanctuary I discovered, or the
research on Malak conducted within.

In short, I can begin my war with them while they are
none the wiser.
"Sanctuary"?!
Quite a pretentious name, huh.
Genetic data... A very interesting term...

And the Cult of Diablos! They get more and more
myterious by the minute.

Same goes for this "Sanctuary" place. It's supposed to
be some ancient lab, but the interior looks kind of,
I don't know—

Not ancient or modern, but more like from an entirely
different era or world... Something like that, right?

Yeah, exactly! This altar looks normal at first
glance, too, but it's impossible to put a finger
on just when or where it's from.

With so many mysteries, all we can do is stay patient
and unravel them one at a time.

Then maybe we should start with this statue. If what
Sergey wrote is correct, solving this puzzle should
get us further inside.
Lady Alpha...can I touch the statue?
...Yes. But do so cautiously and carefully.
Heehee... I'll try it with slime first...
Nothing happened... It feels like...normal stone...

Perhaps the statue itself isn't a mechanism,
but a hint?

But if that were true, there'd be no need for a
statue. There has to be some connection...probably.
Anyway, if we're gonna smash it, leave it to me!

That wouldn't be a great way to start... But it is
possible we might resort to smashing it in the end.
It reacted—
Y-You're...?!

Whoa! She looks just like Lady Alpha! Why?!
I wanna know why!
The statue...became human?!
Not a human, an elf.
That's not the point!
What in the world is—
Lady Alpha!
Who are you...?!
